    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `nvim_echo` is being called directly inside `VimResized` autocommand, it can lead to not updating screen until some forced redraw happens. **But** only after reducing height of terminal emulator.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Create the following autocommand: `au VimResized * lua vim.api.nvim_echo({ { vim.fn.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } }, true, {})`.\r\n3. Reduce height of terminal window (even by 1). Screen is not redrawn.\r\n4. Change width and/or height of terminal emulator in any way. Screen is not redrawn.\r\n5. Press `<Esc>`. Screen is redrawn.\r\n6. Type `:messages` to see that all `VimResized` were triggered properly and `nvim_echo` was properly called multiple times.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nScreen is always redrawn after any change of terminal emulator window dimensions.\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nThis does not happen if `nvim_echo()` is wrapped in `vim.schedule()`. So with this everything works as expected: `au VimResized * lua vim.schedule(function() vim.api.nvim_echo({ { vim.fn.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } }, true, {}) end)`.\r\n\r\nThis also does not happen if not reducing terminal window height. But message is still not shown after every `VimResized`.\r\n\r\n------\r\n\r\nI've bisected it to #25470: it doesn't work on a9a48d6b5f00241e16e7131c997f0117bc5e9047, but does work on 08aea256c8330f482319b0579944a56707cc5bbe. (@bfredl)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1614+ge89071522\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.6.1-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nFrom source",
